The paper presents a novel method for automatic seizure detection based on iEEG data using supervised learning techniques. The paper involves feature extraction and classification, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of iEEG data for seizure detection is related to the field of neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also involves the use of classifiers for channel selection and seizure detection, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method is in the field of epilepsy diagnosis and treatment, which is related to the field of bioinformatics (cs.BIO). Finally, the paper involves the use of signal processing techniques for feature extraction, which is related to the field of signal processing (cs.SI).
